It's just a **Product Requirements Document** in JSON format — a structured task list the agent reads each iteration to know what's done and what's left.

In the Ralph Loop context, it's the file where tasks and their completion status are tracked so the agent can pick up where it left off across iterations, since it can't rely on conversational memory. Something like:

```json
{
  "tasks": [
    { "id": 1, "description": "Set up project structure", "status": "completed" },
    { "id": 2, "description": "Implement auth middleware", "status": "in_progress" },
    { "id": 3, "description": "Write tests", "status": "pending" }
  ]
}
```

It's the "disk as memory" principle — the agent checks this file instead of trying to remember what it did last session.

